                          Voidface — face-region AI blindfold

  Voidface is an open-source system that adds imperceptible perturbations to
  photos and short videos so that face-recognition and face-swap AI pipelines
  either fail to detect a face at all or recover an incorrect identity, while
  the perturbed image remains visually indistinguishable to a human viewer.

  The heart of the project is a small (~10 MB) generator network G, trained
  offline against an adversarial ensemble that includes face detectors,
  identity encoders, diffusion VAEs, CLIP-family encoders, AND — the novel
  element — the face-restoration models (GFPGAN, CodeFormer, Real-ESRGAN)
  that every off-the-shelf face-swap pipeline uses to erase prior defenses.

  At deploy time, applying G to an image is a single forward pass. On an
  Apple-Silicon MacBook it runs in well under a second per image with no
  external GPU. On older hardware it still runs in a few seconds on CPU.

  Voidface is not a shield. It is a defense-in-depth layer. It raises the
  cost of automated face-swap and nudify pipelines and is meant to be used
  in combination with hash-based takedown (StopNCII, Take It Down), content
  provenance (C2PA), and platform policy. See Documentation/limits.md for
  the honest failure modes we know about.


  STATUS

    Read Documentation/status.md for the current shipped state — the
    ensemble targets, restorers, generator, and export paths that
    are real code today vs. still on the roadmap.


  BUILD

    See Documentation/process/contributing.md.

    make install       fetch dependencies (uv)
    make lint          run ruff + mypy
    make test          run pytest
    make bench         run ASR / perceptual benchmarks
    make docs          build documentation site


  USAGE

    Per-image PGD (works today, weights auto-download on first run):

        voidface protect input.jpg -o protected.png --epsilon 12

    Deploy fast path (~500ms per image, needs a trained checkpoint):

        voidface protect input.jpg --use-generator ckpt.pt --face-mask

    Batch a folder of images (generator loaded once):

        voidface protect folder/ --output-dir out/ --use-generator ckpt.pt

    Video with temporal blending:

        voidface protect-video in.mp4 out.mp4 --use-generator ckpt.pt \
            --temporal-blend 0.7 --face-mask

    Train the shipped generator:

        voidface train samples/configs/train_r5_smoke.toml

    Bench with the release ship-gate:

        voidface bench ckpt.pt test-images/ --strict

    Bundle a release (ONNX + int8 + ORT + CoreML + checksums):

        voidface package ckpt.pt release/ --calibration-dir cal/ --coreml
        voidface verify release/

    Export à la carte to every deploy artifact:

        voidface export ckpt.pt out/voidface.onnx \
            --quantize int8 --coreml --ort

    See `voidface --help` for the full workflow reference.


  LAYOUT

    Documentation/     documentation (mirrors src/ layout)
    include/           public API surface (type stubs)
    src/voidface/      core library (training + models + attacks)
    tools/             user-facing programs (CLI, desktop, browser)
    runtime/           shipped deploy runtime (CoreML, ONNX, WASM)
    scripts/           maintenance scripts
    samples/           example configs and sample data
    tests/             unit and integration tests


